---
import '../styles/globals.css';
import BrandingLogo from '../components/BrandingLogo.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'June 2025';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon-32.png" />
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
  <title>Privacy Policy – Zyppi</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Zyppi's Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use and protect your personal data when you use our ride-booking app and website." />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://zyppi.in/privacy-policy" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#673AB7" />
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-900 antialiased">

  <!-- NAV -->
  <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-white/10 bg-[hsl(243_75%_22%)] shadow-lg">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-4xl items-center justify-between px-4 py-4 sm:px-6">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
        <div class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-white p-1.5">
          <img src="/logo.png" alt="Zyppi logo" class="h-6 w-6 object-contain" data-branding-logo />
        </div>
        <span class="text-xl font-bold tracking-wide text-white">ZYPPI</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="text-sm text-white/70 hover:text-white transition-colors">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-600 mb-2">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Effective immediately</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-10 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <p class="text-base">
          Zyppi ("we", "our", or "us") operates the Zyppi mobile application and the website <strong>zyppi.in</strong> (collectively, the "Platform"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share and protect information about you when you use our Platform. By using Zyppi, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Account details:</strong> Full name, email address, mobile number, and profile photo when you register.</li>
          <li><strong>Identity verification:</strong> Government-issued ID, driving licence, vehicle registration certificate and other KYC documents uploaded by drivers and vehicle owners.</li>
          <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> UPI IDs, card details (processed securely by our payment gateway — we do not store full card numbers).</li>
          <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages sent to our support team, feedback and complaint descriptions.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-5 mb-2">1.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Location data:</strong> Precise GPS location when you use the app to book rides, track a driver, or operate as a driver. Location is collected in the foreground (and in the background for active drivers during a trip).</li>
          <li><strong>Device information:</strong> Device type, OS version, unique device identifiers, and IP address.</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, booking history, search queries and crash reports.</li>
          <li><strong>Push notification token:</strong> Used to send ride updates and promotional messages.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>To provide, operate and improve the ride-booking service.</li>
          <li>To match riders with available drivers and share necessary trip details between them (name, phone number, vehicle details, live location) during an active booking.</li>
          <li>To process payments and issue receipts.</li>
          <li>To verify driver and vehicle owner identities and documents before activation.</li>
          <li>To send booking confirmations, OTPs, ride updates and important service notifications.</li>
          <li>To detect fraud, investigate disputes and enforce our Terms & Conditions.</li>
          <li>To comply with applicable Indian laws and respond to lawful government requests.</li>
          <li>To send promotional offers and app updates (you may opt out at any time).</li>
          <li>To conduct analytics and improve app performance and user experience.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">We do not sell your personal data. We share information only in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Between riders and drivers:</strong> During an active booking, limited information (name, photo, phone number, rating) is shared to facilitate the trip.</li>
          <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Trusted third parties who help us operate the Platform (cloud hosting, payment processing, SMS/OTP delivery, analytics). These providers are contractually bound to keep your data confidential.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> When required by law, court order, or to protect the rights and safety of Zyppi, its users or the public.</li>
          <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition or sale of assets, your data may be transferred to the successor entity.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Location Data</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Precise location is the core of our service. We collect it only when the app is in use (foreground) for riders. For active drivers during a live trip, location is collected in the background to enable real-time tracking. You can revoke location permission via your device settings, but this will prevent you from booking or accepting rides. We do not store your historical movement data beyond what is necessary for trip records and dispute resolution.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We retain your account data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services. Trip records are retained for a minimum of 3 years for legal and financial compliance. If you delete your account, personal data is removed within 30 days except where retention is required by law. Anonymised, aggregated data may be retained indefinitely for analytics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We implement industry-standard technical and organisational measures to protect your data, including encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/TLS), secure cloud storage with restricted access, and two-factor authentication for administrative systems. No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure. If you suspect a breach, contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">Under applicable Indian data protection law, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your account and personal data (subject to legal retention obligations).</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent to receive marketing communications.</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with the relevant data protection authority.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3">To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="delete-account">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">8. How to Delete Your Account</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">
          You can permanently delete your Zyppi account and the personal data associated with it at any time, in either of two ways:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>
            <strong>From the app:</strong> Open the Zyppi app, go to <strong>Profile</strong>, tap
            <strong>Delete Account</strong> and confirm. Your account is deactivated immediately.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>By email:</strong> Send a deletion request to
            <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a>
            from your registered email address with the subject "Delete my account". We will verify the
            request and confirm once processing begins.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3">
          After a deletion request, your personal data (profile, saved addresses, uploaded documents) is
          permanently deleted within <strong>30 days</strong>. Trip records that we are legally required to
          keep are retained as described in Section 5 (Data Retention) and deleted when that period ends.
          Account deletion is irreversible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Our Platform is not intended for persons under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If we discover that a minor has created an account, we will delete the account and associated data promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">10. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Our app and website may contain links to third-party services (e.g., Google Maps, payment gateways). This Privacy Policy does not apply to those services. We encourage you to read their privacy policies before providing any personal information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes via app notification or email. Continued use of the Platform after changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          If you have any questions, concerns or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-100 px-5 py-4 text-sm space-y-1">
          <p><strong>Zyppi — Data Privacy Team</strong></p>
          <p>Email &amp; Support: <a href="mailto:admin@zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">admin@zyppi.in</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://zyppi.in" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">https://zyppi.in</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <footer class="bg-gray-900 py-8 mt-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 flex flex-col items-center gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:justify-between">
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">© {new Date().getFullYear()} Zyppi. All rights reserved.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-indigo-400">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a href="/term-condition" class="hover:text-gray-400 transition-colors">Terms & Conditions</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <BrandingLogo />
</body>
</html>
